Dear Guest,
Thanks for flying with us; it's good to have you onboard. We had a great 2010, and there's plenty
on deck for 2011.
We closed out 2010 with a few more "three-peats." With just three years of flying under our
belt, we've swept the reader-based travel awards, including "Best Domestic Airline" in the Condé
Nast Traveler Readers' Choice Awards for the third year running. In December, we received the
highest overall scores or any U.s. airline in the Lagat s global Airline survey or over duve
frequent flyers and took top honors in our category for the third consecutive year.
Are you as proud as we are? Want to shout it from a gadget case, water bottle, t-shirt or hoodie?
Become a fan boy and let your Virgin America flag fly with signature gear from our new Swag
Shop. Just log into in-flight WiFi, go to www.virginamericaswagshop.com, and check out the
goods. While you're browsing, consider giving the gift of better flight to someone who could use
a getaway. The new Virgin America gift certificates are here, our nonstop service to Los Cabos
trom san Francisco is now in tull etect (pertect timing), and our new Tights trom Calitornia to
Cancun start sizzling on January 19-20th. Coincidence? We think not.
Along with our new stops south of the border, we'll be sending the fleet to even more ports of
call in 2011. With more new cities on the horizon, you can expect more blowout bashes like the
Lone Star Launch toasting our first touchdown in Dallas-Fort Worth. We showed revelers a good
time for a good cause with a dance party à la LMFAO and a secret show by outlaw legend Willie
Nelson, all benefitting Stand Up to Cancer. Although the party's over, you can still stand up by
tapping "Make a Difference" in the Shop Section of Red and making a contribution.
Virgin America continues to grow and in spring 2011, we'll be slipping into our new, bigger digs at
SFO's Terminal 2 (T2). Like the San Francisco-based airline that will call it home, T2 will offer
travelers high-end design and a totally unique experience, with mood-lit ticket counters, gates
designed as beautiful "living room" spaces and upscale Slow Food concessions. In addition,
viran Amercas championine Innovative sustalnadle desionto nep make le the new colo
standard in green. We've teamed up with SFO to pursue at least GOLD LEED certification for our
T2 spaces - a first for a major airport terminal in the U.S.
But we digress. We'll let you get back to exploring our ever-evolving selection of TV, movies,
music, food, drinks, and more available on the Red touch screen in front of you. Grab a bite and
enjoy a movie or two. Or, check out our new radio channels as you plug in your laptop, get online
and get some work done. Whatever you do, have a fantastic flight.
Cheers,
Virgin America

score 25 points whenever you check in at a Virgin America location. Set up your account before
landing to grab a few extra points when you grab your bag.
